# The Webport Pivot: Headless Engine & PWA Frontend

Convert [zget](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget) from a standalone TUI into a headless archival server with multiple frontends (TUI, PWA, MCP).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a significant architectural pivot. [zget](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget) will now require a background process (`zget-server`) to be running for full archival capabilities, though the CLI will remain standalone for one-off downloads.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Headless Server (zget-server)

- [NEW] [src/zget/server/app.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/app.py): FastAPI application serving as the central "Archivist's Brain".
- [MODIFY] [src/zget/queue/manager.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/queue/manager.py): Detach queue lifecycle from TUI and move it to the server.
- [NEW] `src/zget/server/routes/`: API endpoints for downloads, search, and library management.

### [Component] PWA Frontend

- [NEW] `src/zget/server/static/`: Mobile-responsive web frontend.
- [NEW] `src/zget/server/static/manifest.json`: PWA manifest for home screen installation.
- Features: Paste URL, Share sheet support (via URL params), Progress bars, and "Download to Camera Roll" (standard browser download).

### [Component] TUI Update

- [MODIFY] `src/zget/tui/app.py`: Update to operate as a client to the local server, or retain an "internal server" mode for zero-config use.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

- `pytest` for the new FastAPI endpoints.
- `zget-mcp` verification against the server.

- Verifying the "Camera Roll" flow (Download -> Save to Files -> Camera Roll).

### [Component] macOS Launch Agent (com.bubroz.zget-server.plist)

- [NEW] `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.bubroz.zget-server.plist`: A macOS background service definition.
- **Config**:
  - Starts `zget-server` on login.
  - Automatically restarts on failure.
  - Logs to `~/Downloads/zget/logs/server.log`.
